-- Ex-divs to take 3.2 points off FTSE 100 on April 16
-- By Tricia Wright
-- Mon Apr 14, 2014 06:33AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, April 14 (Reuters) - The following FTSE 100 <.FTSE> companies will go ex-dividend on Wednesday, after which investors will no longer qualify for the latest dividend payout.     According to Reuters calculations at current market prices, the effect of the resulting adjustment to prices by market-makers would take 3.17 points off the index.

